.\" forgetty.1 — man page for Forgetty terminal emulator
.TH FORGETTY 1 "April 2026" "forgetty 0.1.0-beta" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
forgetty \- the AI\-first agentic terminal emulator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B forgetty
.RB [ \-\-config\-file
.IR path ]
.RB [ \-\-working\-directory
.IR path ]
.RB [ \-\-class
.IR name ]
.RB [ \-e
.IR command
.RI [ args... ]]
.br
.B forgetty \-\-version
.br
.B forgetty \-\-help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Forgetty
is a workspace\-aware terminal emulator where your AI agents, tabs,
splits, and sessions persist across reboots and sync across devices.
Built on GTK4/libadwaita with the Ghostty VT engine for high\-performance
terminal rendering.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-config\-file " path"
Path to configuration file. If not specified, the default configuration
is used.
.TP
.BI \-\-working\-directory " path"
Set the initial working directory for the shell session.
.TP
.BI \-\-class " name"
Set the window class (WM_CLASS) for window manager rules. Useful for
per\-window configuration in tiling window managers.
.TP
.BI \-e " command " "\fR[\fIargs...\fR]"
Execute a command instead of the default shell. All arguments after
.B \-e
are passed to the command. Flags like
.B \-\-working\-directory
must come before
.BR \-e .
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version number and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print usage information and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SHELL
The default shell to launch if no
.B \-e
flag is given and no
.B shell
key is set in config.toml. If
.B $SHELL
is unset or points to a nonexistent path, Forgetty consults the user's
.I /etc/passwd
entry via
.BR getpwuid (3).
If that also fails, falls back to
.BR /bin/sh .
.TP
.B TERM
Set by Forgetty to advertise terminal capabilities.
.TP
.B FORGETTY_CONFIG
If set, used as the default configuration file path.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/forgetty/config.toml
User configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/libghostty\-vt.so.0
Shared Ghostty VT library used for terminal emulation.
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/dev.forgetty.Forgetty.desktop
Desktop entry for GNOME and other desktop environments.
